cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.PF 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with power allocation in cellular networks. It could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) as it uses utility functions to represent different users' modulation schemes. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it presents a distributed algorithm for power allocation. It may also fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) as it discusses modulation schemes and transmission of packets. Finally, it could be classified under cs.PF (Performance) as it aims to optimize power allocation to maximize performance.
